Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide fries (no need to peel).

Pop the fries onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pop the @British Hickory Smoked Sausages{2%units} onto a baking tray and bake on the middle shelf until golden brown and cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The sausages are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Slice the @Brioche Hot Dog Buns{2%units} down through the middle (but not all the way through).

In a #small bowl{}, mix together the @hot sauce{30%grams} and @honey{15%grams} to make your hot honey glaze.

Just before everything's ready, pop the buns onto a baking tray and into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Pop the buns onto your #plates{}, spread the @ranch dressing{30%grams} inside the buns and fill with the sausages. Drizzle over the hot honey sauce to finish.

Serve the @wild rocket{20%grams} and fries alongside.

Drizzle the @balsamic glaze{12%milliliters} over the rocket and serve the fries with @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp} for dipping.